How to Write a Formula in Excel
Select the Cell:

Click on the cell where you want to enter the formula.
Enter an Equals Sign:

Type = to indicate that you're entering a formula.
Example of a Formula:

To calculate the product of values in cells A3 and C3:
In cell E3, type: =A3*C3
Press Enter.
Apply the Formula to Other Cells:

Select cell E3.
Drag the fill handle (small square at the bottom right corner) down to E12.
The formula will be applied to all selected cells.
Functions Covered:
SUM
AVERAGE
MAX
MIN
XLOOKUP
SUMPRODUCT
OFFSET
QUERY
